    <div>
        <h1>How to Whitelist a Domain in Microsoft 365 for a PhishSims.com Phishing Campaign</h1>

        <p>In this guide, we'll walk through the steps to whitelist a domain for a phishing campaign on PhishSims.com in Microsoft 365.</p>


        <ol>
            <li>
                <h2>Sign in to your Microsoft 365 Defender portal</h2>
                <p>Visit <code>https://portal.office.com</code> and log in with your credentials.</p>
            
            </li>
            <li>
                <h2>Navigate to Policies & rules</h2>
                <p>Click on "Policies & rules" in the left-hand menu.</p>
            <img src="/img/Listing1.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            </li>
            <li>
                <h2>Choose Threat policies</h2>
                <p>Under "Policies & rules," select "Threat policies."</p>
            <img src="/img/Listing2.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            </li>
            <li>
                <h2>Select Anti-spam inbound policy (Default)</h2>
                <p>Look for the "Anti-spam inbound policy (Default)" option and click on it.</p>
            <img src="/img/Listing3.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            </li>
            <li>
                <h2>Edit allowed and blocked senders and domains</h2>
                <p>Scroll down and click on "Edit allowed and blocked senders and domains."</p>
            <img src="/img/Listing4.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            </li>
            <li>
                <h2>Click on Allow domains</h2>
                <p>Within the settings, click on "Allow domains."</p>
            <img src="/img/Listing5.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            </li>
            <li>
                <h2>Add the domain to whitelist</h2>
                <p>Enter the domain provided during the setup of the phishing campaign on PhishSims.com.</p>
            <p><strong>Note:</strong> Please note: The domain is provided when selecting the template during the set up of the phishing campaign. </p>
            <img src="/img/Listing6.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            </li>
            <li>
                <h2>Click Add domains</h2>
                <p>After adding the domain, click on "Add domains" to confirm.</p>
            <img src="/img/Listing7.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            </li>
            <li>
                <h2>Save changes</h2>
                <p>Finally, click on "Save" to apply the changes.</p>
            <img src="/img/Listing8.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            </li>
        </ol>

        <p>Congratulations! 🎉 You've successfully whitelisted the domain on PhishSims.com in Microsoft 365. Emails sent via this specific phishing domain will now bypass the spam filter.</p>

        <p><strong>Note:</strong> Remember that each phishing campaign on PhishSims.com uses a separate domain. Make sure to whitelist any new domains before launching future campaigns.</p>

